cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper deals with the complexity of two-player games played on graphs, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of measures such as Inf, Sup, LimInf, LimSup, and WMP suggests a connection to mathematical logic (cs.LO) and the study of quantitative systems (cs.DS). The mention of Boolean combinations of constraints and the study of parameterized complexity suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the synthesis of reactive systems (cs.SY).
